<p class="stars">★★★★★</p>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> Travel nurses on multiple assignments per year</p>
<p><strong>Columns:</strong> Contract start/end | Agency | Hospital | City/State | Pay rate | Housing | Contact info | Renewal status</p>
<p><strong>Also includes:</strong> Tax home tracking, state license log, CEU hour tracker, professional reference tracker</p>
<p><strong>Why it's essential:</strong> Travel nurses touch 3–5 agencies and 6–10 facilities per year. Keeping this organized in one physical book saves hours of digging through emails at tax time.</p>
<p><strong>Price:</strong> $11.99 on Amazon KDP</p>
</div>

<h2>Best for New Graduate Nurses</h2>

<div class="product">
<h3>New Grad RN Orientation Progress Log</h3>
<p class="stars">★★★★☆</p>
<p><strong>Best for:</strong> New grads in nurse residency programs (12–18 month orientations)</p>
<p><strong>Columns:</strong> Week | Preceptor | Unit | Skills practiced | Competencies signed off | Goals for next week</p>
<p><strong>Also includes:</strong> NCLEX score page, license # tracker, 90-day/180-day/1-year reflection prompts</p>
<p><strong>Why it works:</strong> Residency programs move fast. This log lets you track your growth without relying on your manager's records — useful during annual reviews.</p>
