<h2>What to Look for in Any Nursing Log Book</h2>

<p><strong>Lay-flat binding:</strong> You're writing on the go, often standing. A book that stays open without you holding it down is worth the extra $2.</p>

<p><strong>Pre-formatted columns:</strong> Generic lined journals don't work for clinical data. You want columns matched to your specialty's actual workflow.</p>

<p><strong>6×9 size:</strong> Fits in a white coat pocket or scrub pocket. Anything bigger stays in the locker and doesn't get used.</p>

<p><strong>Enough pages:</strong> A 50-page book lasts 3 months. A 120-page book lasts a year. Buy once.</p>

